Stocks pulled back below their recent record levels on Wall Street Monday as the marketâ€™s momentum slowed down following its best week since February. The S&P 500, the Dow Jones Industrial Average and the tech-heavy Nasdaq fell. Technology, energy and travel-related companies had some of the biggest losses.On Monday:The S&P 500 fell 43.05 points, or 0.9%, to 4,668.97.The Dow Jones Industrial Average fell 320.04 points, or 0.9%, to 35,650.95.The Nasdaq fell 217.32 points, or 1.4%, to 15,413.28.The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies fell 31.31 points, or 1.4%, to 2,180.50.For the year:The S&P 500 is up 912.90 points, or 24.3%.The Dow is up 5,044.47 points, or 16.5%.The Nasdaq is up 2,525 points, or 19.6%.The Russell 2000 is up 205.64 points, or 10.4%.